HC Bonum, in partnership with Digital Jewels, AT3 Resources and DB Consulting, has unveiled a work-from-home survey for Nigerian professionals. The firms, in a statement on Monday, described the survey as the first of its kind since the COVID-19 pandemic that altered “the way we work.” According to the statement, the survey is expected to assist business leaders understand the benefits and challenges of adapting to the work-from-home arrangement in a post-coronavirus world. The Managing Director, HC Bonum, Lanre Onasanya, said, “The WFH Survey is our contribution to the workplace ecosystem, to support leaders in decision making,  professionals in adapting to the new world order and the economy in recovering from the effects of Covid-19.” “By now, we all agree a new work culture is imminent and leading our businesses through this disruptive period is crucial, hence the survey,” the Managing Partner, AT3 Resources Limited, Tosin Adefeko, said. According to the statement, all working professionals are invited to participate to enable the firms to make meaningful comparisons and insightful analysis that can guide organisations as they emerge from the current realities. Copyright PUNCH.
